<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="693" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d693">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cambon</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">French
                                        Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-08-29"><hi rend="italic">August 29,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The French embassy has just received a telegram from Habana in which
                            Captain-General Blanco expresses the wish to know whether the Federal
                            Government would see any objection to officers of the Spanish army
                            returning singly to Spain by way of the United States.</p>
                        <p>The French embassy would be much obliged to the Department of State if it
                            would enable it to reply to this question by telegram.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>